The paper deals with visual navigation using deep reinforcement learning, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The proposed AI2-THOR framework involves interaction with objects and physics engine, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and system engineering (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed model, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG).
